<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE0191">
<l>ellāru meṉṉum paṭarkkai viṟutiyu</l>
<l>mellīru meṉṉu muṉṉilai viṟutiyu</l>
<l>moṟṟu mukaramuṅ keṭumeṉa moḻipa</l>
<l>niṟṟal vēṇṭum rakarap puḷḷi</l>
<l>yummai nilaiyu miṟuti yāṉa</l>
<l>tammiṭai varūum paṭarkkai mēṉa</l>
<l>nummiṭai varūu muṉṉilai moḻikkē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>In the endings of <foreign xml:lang="ta">ellārum</foreign> which denotes the third person,<note place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">paṭarkkai.</foreign></note></l>
<l>and of <foreign xml:lang="ta">ellīrum</foreign> which denotes the second person,<note place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">muṉṉilai.</foreign></note></l>
<l>the consonant and the sound <foreign xml:lang="ta">u</foreign> disappear ;</l>
<l>so it is said ;</l>
<l>the non-vocalized consonant <foreign xml:lang="ta">r</foreign> must remain ;</l>
<l>and <foreign xml:lang="ta">um</foreign> stands as final ;</l>
<l><foreign xml:lang="ta">tam</foreign> comes in between in the third person</l>
<l>and <foreign xml:lang="ta">num</foreign> comes in between with the words of the second person.<note place="foot">Exx. : <foreign xml:lang="ta">ellārum + ai &gt; ēllār-tam-m-ai-y-um ; ellīrum + oṭu &gt; ellīr -num-m-oṭu-um.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
